caption: Table 1: Summary of existing regret bounds. g is the expected valuation function, F is the c.d.f. of the noise, and π(x, p) is the reward for price p and context x, defined in Section 2.1.
description: This table summarizes existing regret bounds from various research papers on dynamic pricing.  It compares different models (linear and non-parametric) and assumptions about the noise distribution (e.g., known, parametric, Lipschitz continuous).  The regret bounds represent the performance of different pricing algorithms, indicating how much revenue is lost compared to an optimal strategy.
